<span id="freeTextContainer11976532924336974545">An otherwise intriguing story alternately infused with unimaginably boring historical information. McLaurin takes absolutely no liberties in speculating anything--emotions, actions, words, nothing. One line went something like, &quot;Although we can never know how Celia reacted to her rape, we can speculate that she was scared and upset.&quot; Really? You think so? A very historically accurate read with little emotional appeal.</span>
