        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1535658413" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14427628177808420652">It&apos;s hard to write good history books, and Celia, A Slave was, in my opinion, a perfect example of what NOT to do when writing a book about historical events. It was dry, overly detailed, and didn&apos;t catch my attention at all. (except the bit where the author went into meticulous detail about the disposal of the body. It was so gruesome.) It&apos;s too bad, because Celia&apos;s story is actually quite interesting, and I would have been enthusiastic about reading this if it had been told in a more captivati</span>
  <span id="freeText14427628177808420652" style="display:none">It's hard to write good history books, and Celia, A Slave was, in my opinion, a perfect example of what NOT to do when writing a book about historical events. It was dry, overly detailed, and didn't catch my attention at all. (except the bit where the author went into meticulous detail about the disposal of the body. It was so gruesome.) It's too bad, because Celia's story is actually quite interesting, and I would have been enthusiastic about reading this if it had been told in a more captivating way. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14427628177808420652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

